CLUB WORLD®
WINE LIST
CHAMPAGNE
Charles Heidsieck, Brut Réserve
Superb, rich and luxuriant fruit together with toasty vanilla flavours
combine in this delightful champagne.
WHITE WINES
Geyser Peak Chardonnag, 1985
A lovely example of Chardonnay from the Sonoma Valley.
This wine features concentrated ripe fruit and gentle oak in perfect balance
Great with seafood, poultry and white meat dishes.
Sancerre Cuvée des Anges, 1995,
Fouassier
Fresh grassy and gooseberry flavours prevail in this delicious wine. It is a
delightful aperitif which is also good with seafood,
asparagus and light dishes.

RED WINES
Buena Vista Cabernet Sauvignon, 1993
This wine has rich, full-bodied Cabernet fruit
of impressive concentration from the oldest winery in California.
It is particularly good with red meat and cheese.
OR
Fetzer Barrel, Select Zinfandel, 1994
Zinfandel, the mystery grape of California thought to be identical
to the Primitivo of Southern Italy, produces a range of wine styles
from blush to port. This wine is packed full of blackberry fruit
and spicy oak. It complements red meat, poultry and most cheese.
ONE OF THE FOLLOWING WILL ALSO BE AVAILABLE:
Chateau Citran, 1993
Concentrated blackcurrant fruit combined with complex oak flavours
gives this claret structure and finesse. It is recommended
with red meat and cheese dishes.
OR
Cortegiano, 1991, Vino da TavolA di Toscana
This rich and full-bodied wine is a blend of Cabernet Sauvignon
and Sangioveto from Tuscany in the heart of Italy. The barrel ageing adds a
touch of vanilla to its aroma. Its palate is balanced and long.
THERE WILL BE A COMPLIMENTARY BAR AVAILABLE
SERVING ALCOHOLIC BEVERAGES AND SOFT DRINKS
